WEBVTT

00:00.795 --> 00:02.536
NARRATOR:
In the criminal justice system

00:02.597 --> 00:06.511
the people are represented by two
separate yet equally important groups,

00:06.568 --> 00:08.377
the police
who investigate crime

00:08.436 --> 00:11.212
and the district attorneys
who prosecute the offenders.

00:11.273 --> 00:12.911
These are their stories.

00:14.042 --> 00:15.851
You ain't got no J.
Come on. What you want?

00:16.044 --> 00:17.250
Oh!
I'm just warming up!

00:17.379 --> 00:19.017
Hey, Ms. G,
check this out!

00:19.080 --> 00:20.354
You want in? Slam dunk.

00:20.415 --> 00:22.759
Yeah. Hey, you want to impress
me, next time you get a job,

00:22.817 --> 00:25.388
show up five minutes before your
shift and not five minutes after.

00:25.487 --> 00:27.262
Their clock was fast,
just like me.

00:27.322 --> 00:29.598
The world is fast, Robert. Sometimes
you gotta run to keep up.

00:29.658 --> 00:30.728
(SCOFFS)

00:30.792 --> 00:31.964
Anyway, check this...
What?

00:32.027 --> 00:35.201
Check this now, Jordan,
Jordan goes for the three.

00:35.263 --> 00:36.537
He shoots.
He misses!

00:36.598 --> 00:37.906
Come on, man. I made that!

00:37.966 --> 00:39.172
(sun FIRING)

00:40.068 --> 00:41.342
(PEOPLE EXCLAIMING)

00:49.711 --> 00:51.315
ROBERT: Call 911. Somebody!

00:52.447 --> 00:55.189
Anybody in the neighborhood
have a beef with Ms. Gaylin?

00:55.383 --> 00:56.623
No one mess with Ms. G.

00:56.685 --> 00:59.666
You got a problem? She'd sit
with you long as it takes.

00:59.721 --> 01:02.201
Like little Lee, when his
mama had the swollen ankles,

01:02.357 --> 01:04.803
she straightened out what they needed
to get the prescription, you know.

01:04.858 --> 01:06.861
Right. I think
it was a drive-by.

01:06.928 --> 01:08.805
A drive-by?
Why, you hear a car?

01:08.863 --> 01:09.898
Mmm-hmm.

01:09.964 --> 01:11.034
All right. Thanks.

01:11.099 --> 01:12.134
You didn't hear a car?

01:12.334 --> 01:13.540
(CHATTERING OVER POLICE RADIO)

01:13.601 --> 01:14.705
She walked on water.

01:14.769 --> 01:16.271
And nobody saw anything.

01:16.338 --> 01:17.544
Somebody that popular,

01:17.605 --> 01:19.710
maybe one of the other
social workers was jealous.

01:19.774 --> 01:21.776
I don't know. One of the
kids thought he heard a car.

01:21.843 --> 01:25.120
Let's tell the uni's that
are doing the canvassing.

01:26.715 --> 01:27.921
You in charge?

01:27.982 --> 01:29.962
Detective Briscoe,
Detective Curtis.

01:30.018 --> 01:33.431
Doug Gaylin, Jennifer's father.
I got a call.

01:33.521 --> 01:34.932
What do we know so far?

01:34.989 --> 01:37.833
Well, so far, not too
much, unfortunately.

